Hey there 🙂 As you can see I’ve bought a few products from the newest Dior collection. I know the lip butter is controversial one because of not the best formula and the tube isn’t full while we have to pay 33£. As often with luxury items we often pay for the logo not the quality, and it’s a bit ridiculous because if we pay more the quality should be exceptional. If it comes to mine, is not as bad in comparison what other people got but it’s still far from being full. Would I buy it again, don’t think so, my mistake was to get it on launch day instead of waiting for a few days, in this case I would buy another blush stick.

🔍 Product Overview
	•	Brand: Alpha‑H (Australian skincare brand known for its active, results-driven formulas)
	•	Product Type: Exfoliating polish
	•	Texture: Creamy with fine polishing granules
	•	Best For: Dull, uneven, congested, or rough-textured skin

⸻

🌟 Key Features & Benefits
	•	Dual Exfoliation: Combines natural cellulose microbeads (physical) and fruit enzymes (chemical) for effective but gentle exfoliation.
	•	Brightening Effect: Helps reduce dullness and enhances radiance.
	•	Improves Texture: Smooths rough patches and reduces the appearance of enlarged pores.
	•	Enzyme Action: Gently dissolves dead skin cells without harsh acids.

⸻

🧪 Notable Ingredients
	•	Pomegranate & Papaya Enzymes – Gently exfoliate and brighten skin.

	•	Lactic Acid (in some versions) – A mild AHA that hydrates while exfoliating
